All public schools will receive tablets by June next year, ICT Principal Secretary Sammy Itemere has said. In the pilot project, 11,500 pupils from 150 schools received tablets, laptops and projectors. Itemere said the government has received 100,000 laptops out of 1.2 million to be distributed.He spoke at Siginon Global Logistics, Mombasa. The tablets are being manufactured in China in partnership with Portugal and Brazil, Itemere said. They will cost Sh28 billion.